track_notes: Start at the Arizona Trail TH on Canelo Pass Rd.  Hike in about 3 miles before a steep but fairly short bushwhack.
track_title: Lookout Knoll UP via Arizona Trail

track_notes: This is the down version of the track

The hike to Lookout Knoll using this track is a 1.5 mile bushwhack to the summit with 1100+ feet of elevation gain and an average slope of 14 degrees. The brush can get pretty thick in spots and the slope steep and slippery with loose rock. However, most of the time you can avoid the thickest underbrush by cleverly looking for open spots to progress forward and sometimes crawling under a barbed wire fence. There are no tall trees on the summit so either bring a mast or use the scrub on the summit that can reach as high as 15-20 feet.
This was our return trip from the summit to the car. In general it followed a similar route as the ascent.
